{
  "texts": [
    "In this situation, private schools generally demand at least two tests for each bimester, while public schools generally demand only one.",
    "There is practically a consensus among educators on the importance of assessment tests to identify how well the student understood the content studied.",
    "However, despite this, our results indicate that almost 86% of Brazilian K-12 science teachers, who work in public schools, only apply the minimum number of tests currently required.",
    "This conduct goes against the trend advocated in several studies related to the importance of the use of formative assessments (Boström and Palm, 2023).",
    "Maybe this is due to the low weekly workload that science subjects have had in Brazil in the last few years (Moreira, 2018)."
  ]
}